This paper focuses on the analysis of recurrent neural networks, specifically long short-term memory networks, which are commonly used for sequence modeling. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of visual analysis tools, which could also place it in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the analysis of datasets containing chord progressions and phrase structure, which could suggest a connection to Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
